  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_0' aria-label=\" Mohammad Afzal Mohammad Sharif versus The State of Maharashtra and Others pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('0','2025','2025_10_78_93','2025INSC1100'); ><font size='4'> <strong>MOHAMMAD AFZAL MOHAMMAD SHARIF<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>THE STATE OF MAHARASHTRA AND OTHERS </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 10 S.C.R. 78</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 1100</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010004092025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : SANJAY KUMAR<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, SATISH CHANDRA SHARMA</strong><br> Issue for Consideration The complaint of the appellant before the High Court was that the police officers concerned had failed in their duty by not registering a First Information Report apropos the attack and assault on him by four individuals on 13.05.2023. The Division Court dismissed his writ petition, suspecting his bonafides. Headnotes&dagger; Penal Code, 1860 &ndash; s.307 r/w. ss.34, 324, 325, 326 &ndash; This litigation has its moorings in the communal riots that broke out in Akola City, Maharashtra, on 13.05.2023 owing to a social media post &ndash; The<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 11-09-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CRIMINAL APPEAL No. 3976/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Appeal(s) allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('0','2025','2025_10_78_93','2025INSC1100','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Spli